    "source_target": "third_party/curvytron-reference",
    "source_commit": "8fec14c",
    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for source Game.removeAvatar() during an active three-player round after one avatar has already died.",
      "The harness starts a real source round, waits for delayed PrintManager.start timers, forces avatar 3 into a wall death, parks avatar 1 on a clean warmdown lane, then removes avatar 2.",
      "It proves the leave emits player:leave, destroys the leaver to present=false/alive=false, does not add the leaver to the current Game.deaths collection, and immediately emits round:end when only avatar 1 remains alive.",
      "Survivor scoring uses the full avatar collection size, so avatar 1 receives two round points even though avatar 2 is non-present at round resolution.",
      "At game:stop the source does not emit end because avatar 3 is still present; it resizes to the two present avatars and starts a next round where avatar 2 is non-present and appears in deaths."
    ]
  },
